      "type": "edit",
      "id": "90f271961123b377",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "90f271961123b377",
        "text": "Accordingly, these are (cum grano salis) metaphysical concepts that are built into a socially fungible, nevertheless curious anthropology that education needs in order to keep its operativity plausible. It has to be this way because it could not be otherwise, and for precisely this reason one can speak of an ontology still and successfully functioning in relation to the address form of education, which nevertheless hangs on the cant hook of axioms otherwise long since traded as problematic.26 And it is downright astonishing that the determinants of that (anthropo)ontology are rather aggravatedly claimed and in the course of the reform rage of the educational system are undauntedly held on to and increased by incessantly overtaking reforms and reforms of reforms, so much so that one can get the impression, that this holding on and this increase is actually what it is all about, irrespective of the fact that neither philosophy nor sociology, in their serious forms, can provide justifications for what is for education an indispensable structural feature in the generation of its social addresses."
